&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt; that  &lt;code&gt;‚Äò0‚Äô&lt;/code&gt;  (zero) and  &lt;code&gt;‚ÄòO‚Äô&lt;/code&gt;  (the letter) are considered the same character and therefore &lt;strong&gt;ONLY&lt;/strong&gt; the letter  &lt;code&gt;‚ÄòO‚Äô&lt;/code&gt;  is a valid character.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;input&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#input&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Input&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Input consists of strings (one per line) each of which will consist of one to twenty valid characters. There will be no invalid characters in any of the strings. Your program should read to the end of file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;output&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;anchor&#34; href=&#34;#output&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt; Output&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For each input string, you should print the string starting in column 1 immediately followed by exactly one of the following strings.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;STRING&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;th style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;CRITERIA&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/thead&gt;
&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;‚Äò -- is not a palindrome.‚Äô&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;if the string is not a palindrome and is not a mirrored string&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;‚Äò -- is a regular palindrome.‚Äô&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;if the string is a palindrome and is not a mirrored string&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;‚Äò -- is a mirrored string.‚Äô&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;if the string is not a palindrome and is a mirrored string&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;‚Äò -- is a mirrored palindrome.‚Äô&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td style=&#34;text-align:center&#34;&gt;if the string is a palindrome and is a mirrored string&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
